-- Conoco says one Louisiana refinery shut; 2nd shutting down
-- 
-- Mon Sep 1, 2008 11:05am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/01/us-storm-gustav-energy-conocophillips-idUSN3122455820080901

 

 HOUSTON  (Reuters) - ConocoPhillps said on Sunday night its 247,000 barrel per day (bpd) Alliance, Louisiana, refinery near New Orleans was completely shut ahead of approaching Hurricane Gustav. 

 Conoco's 239,000 bpd Lake Charles, Louisiana, refinery continues to shut down. (Reporting by  Erwin Seba ; Editing by Kim Coghill)